'''Calçado''' is a city located in the state of [[Pernambuco]], [[Brazil]]. Located at 200&nbsp;km away from [[Recife]], capital of the state of Pernambuco. Has an estimated ([[Brazilian Institute of Geography and Statistics|Ibge 2009]]) population of 11,619 inhabitants.
==Geography== * State - [[Pernambuco]] * Region - [[Agreste|Agreste Pernambucano]] * Boundaries - [[Lajedo, Pernambuco|Lajedo]] ('''N''' and '''E'''); [[Canhotinho]] ('''S'''); [[Angelim]] and [[Jupi]] ('''W''') * Area - 423.08&nbsp;km<sup>2</sup> * Elevation - 643 m * Hydrography - [[Mundaú River|Mundaú]] and [[Una River (Pernambuco)|Una rivers]] * Vegetation - [[Caatinga]] [[Hiperxerófila]] * Clima - Hot and humid * Annual average temperature - 22.1 c * Distance to [[Recife]] - 200&nbsp;km
==Economy== The main economic activities in '''Calçado''' are based in [[agribusiness]], especially [[manioc]], [[beans]]; and [[livestock]] such as [[cattle]], [[sheep]] and [[poultry]].
